data.meta_description: Gisela of Neustria was the elder daughter of the Emperor Louis I  the Pious  (816 – 840) and his second wife Judith of Altdorf, the daughter of Welf II, Count of Altdorf, and was full sister to the Emperor Charles II  the Bald  (875 – 877).
